            <h3>Speciality</h3>
            <h4>Ophthalmology (Eyes)</h4>
            <p>Ophthalmology is the branch of medicine specializing in eye care, including diagnosis, treatment, and surgery for vision disorders, eye diseases, and injuries.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <img src="~/images/bones.png" alt="Orthopedics">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Speciality</h3>
            <h4>Orthopedics (Bones)</h4>
            <p>Orthopedics (or Orthopaedics) is the medical and surgical specialty focused on the bones, joints, muscles, ligaments, tendons, and nerves that make up the musculoskeletal system. </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <img src="~/images/pediatrics.png" alt="Pediatrics">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Speciality</h3>
            <h4>Pediatrics and New Born (Child)</h4>
            <p>
                Pediatrics is the branch of medicine dedicated to the health and medical care of infants, children, and adolescents (up to 18-21 years). Neonatology is a subspecialty focusing on newborns (especially premature or critically ill babies).
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <img src="~/images/pain.png" alt="Pain Management">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Speciality</h3>
            <h4>Pain Management</h4>
            <p>Pain management is a medical specialty focused on diagnosing, treating, and preventing acute and chronic pain to improve quality of life. It combines medications, therapies, procedures, and lifestyle strategies tailored to each patient’s needs.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
